      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 605: 🔴 Critical Issues - The restore state is kept only in memory, but the daemon account active state can outlive the Android process. If the app is killed after `deactivateProxyAccountsForBackground()` runs, `backgroundDeactivatedAccounts` is recreated empty on the next launch/push, so foreground restore or push restore has no account ids to reactivate and proxy accounts can remain offline indefinitely. Persist the background-deactivated ids, and clear them only after a successful restore or terminal account configuration change. For example:\n```suggestion\nprivate val backgroundDeactivatedAccounts \u003d loadBackgroundDeactivatedAccounts().toMutableSet()\n\nprivate fun markBackgroundDeactivated(accountId: String) {\n    backgroundDeactivatedAccounts.add(accountId)\n    saveBackgroundDeactivatedAccounts(backgroundDeactivatedAccounts)\n}\n\nprivate fun clearBackgroundDeactivated(accountId: String) {\n    backgroundDeactivatedAccounts.remove(accountId)\n    saveBackgroundDeactivatedAccounts(backgroundDeactivatedAccounts)\n}\n```\nThen use these helpers in deactivate, restore, explicit deactivate, and remove-account paths.",
      "revId": "577c19e8dfc02a44335101b1ccb8e2f02c8b090e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
